Imagine you are a data scientist analyzing a year’s worth of weather data, recorded every 10 minutes throughout 2020. This dataset captures 21 key meteorological indicators—temperature, humidity, and more—painting a detailed picture of the atmosphere in motion. Your mission is: Uncover hidden patterns, detect anomalies, and forecast future weather trends. Identify seasonal shifts, extreme conditions, and the intricate relationships between variables. Deliver structured insights that are actionable, interpretable, and valuable for climate monitoring, forecasting, and environmental research.
